---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Privacy Policy — QR Guy" 
  description="Learn about the privacy-first model of QR Guy. We process all data locally. 0% server storage, 0% tracking, 100% security."
  canonicalUrl="https://qrguy.com/privacy-policy"
>
  <Header />

  <main class="flex-grow relative bg-canvas py-16 md:py-24 px-6 md:px-8 font-sans">
    <!-- Premium Mesh Gradient Background -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 overflow-hidden pointer-events-none -z-10" aria-hidden="true">
      <div class="absolute top-[-20%] left-[-15%] w-[65%] h-[65%] rounded-full bg-violet/10 dark:bg-violet/5 blur-[100px] md:blur-[130px] animate-mesh-1"></div>
      <div class="absolute bottom-[-15%] right-[-10%] w-[55%] h-[60%] rounded-full bg-highlight-pink/10 dark:bg-highlight-pink/5 blur-[90px] md:blur-[120px] animate-mesh-3"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="max-w-[800px] mx-auto">
      <!-- Tag / Badge -->
      <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-1 mb-6 rounded-full border border-hairline bg-canvas-soft-2 text-[11px] font-mono text-body">
        <span class="inline-block w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-success"></span>
        Last Updated: June 10, 2026
      </div>

      <!-- Main Heading -->
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-semibold text-ink tracking-tight mb-8 leading-[1.1] select-none">
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>

      <!-- Lead paragraph -->
      <p class="text-lg text-body font-light leading-relaxed mb-12">
        At QR Guy, we respect your right to privacy and security. That's why we engineered this tool to operate on a <strong>zero-data retention model</strong>. Everything you generate or scan stays entirely on your own device.
      </p>

      <!-- Policy Content Blocks -->
      <div class="space-y-10 text-sm text-body leading-relaxed">
        
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink tracking-tight border-b border-hairline pb-2">1. Client-Side Execution</h2>
          <p>
            Unlike traditional web tools, QR Guy executes all generation algorithms, styling renders, and barcode decoding natively in your browser sandbox. 
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1.5 text-xs text-mute pl-2">
            <li>Your input content (URLs, numbers, Wi-Fi parameters, vCard contacts) is converted to a QR layout using local client-side Javascript.</li>
            <li>No database or remote service log tracks the parameters you paste or input.</li>
            <li>Once the workspace is loaded, you can disconnect your internet and continue generating and styling codes.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink tracking-tight border-b border-hairline pb-2">2. Processing of Custom Logos & Images</h2>
          <p>
            If you upload a custom logo to embed in your QR design, the image is read by the web browser using the HTML5 <strong>FileReader API</strong> and converted into a local Base64 Data URL. The file is never sent to any server, storage system, or external API.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink tracking-tight border-b border-hairline pb-2">3. Scanner & Camera Permissions</h2>
          <p>
            When utilizing the QR and Barcode Scanner tab, the web app requests access to your camera. The video feed is analyzed frame-by-frame entirely inside local memory using canvas render elements. 
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1.5 text-xs text-mute pl-2">
            <li>No camera frames, image pixels, or decoded strings are sent to third parties.</li>
            <li>The camera permission can be revoked instantly at any time in your browser settings.</li>
            <li>You can also scan QR codes by uploading image files, which are processed entirely locally.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink tracking-tight border-b border-hairline pb-2">4. Cookies and Local Storage</h2>
          <p>
            We do not use tracking cookies, analytics pixels, or advertisement trackers.
          </p>
          <p>
            To enhance your design workflow, we use the browser's <code>localStorage</code> cache. This allows QR Guy to remember:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1.5 text-xs text-mute pl-2">
            <li>Your visual theme preference (Light or Dark mode).</li>
            <li>The latest design configurations you styled (colors, shapes, corner styling, error correction levels) so you don't have to rebuild them on your next visit.</li>
            <li>The local scan history log, which you can clear manually at any time with a single click.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            All localStorage keys remain stored inside your browser client and can be wiped instantly by clearing your browser cache.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink tracking-tight border-b border-hairline pb-2">5. Updates to This Policy</h2>
          <p>
            Because we do not store emails or profile data, we cannot notify users of policy updates. Any changes will be posted directly to this URL with an updated timestamp.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Contact support note -->
        <div class="p-6 rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-canvas-soft-2/50 backdrop-blur-sm mt-8">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-ink mb-2">Privacy Inquiries</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-mute leading-relaxed">
            If you have security questions or wish to audit the open-source code base, please visit our <a href="https://github.com/Aftab016/qr-guy.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-link hover:underline">GitHub Repository</a> or contact us directly at <span class="font-mono text-ink text-[11px]">privacy@qrguy.com</span>.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
